HEADWORD: Manhole
<hw>Man"hole`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A hole through which
a man may descend or creep into a drain, sewer, steam boiler, parts of
machinery, etc., for cleaning or repairing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Manhood</ent>⟦br⟧
